# Sample Spec-Kit Configuration File

This is a sample configuration for a Spec-Kit Plus project that demonstrates the configuration structure:

```yaml
project:
  name: "AI/Spec-Driven Book Creation"
  description: "A project to create books using spec-driven methodology with AI assistance"
  version: "1.0.0"
  constitution: "./.specify/memory/constitution.md"

directories:
  specs: "./specs"
  plans: "./specs/*/plan.md"
  tasks: "./specs/*/tasks.md"
  history: "./history"
  prompts: "./history/prompts"
  adrs: "./history/adr"

templates:
  spec: "./.specify/templates/spec-template.md"
  plan: "./.specify/templates/plan-template.md"
  tasks: "./.specify/templates/tasks-template.md"

commands:
  spec: "./.specify/scripts/bash/create-new-feature.sh"
  plan: "./.specify/scripts/bash/setup-plan.sh"
  tasks: "./.specify/scripts/bash/check-prerequisites.sh"
```

This configuration demonstrates:
- Project metadata
- Directory structure for specifications, plans, and tasks
- Template locations
- Available commands